ference for a sharp\nsoftening around nuclear density followed by stiffening around twice nuclear\ndensity, consistent with a strong first-order phase transition. While the\nstatistical evidence in favor of new physics within NS cores remains tenuous\nwith GW170817 alone, these tantalizing hints reemphasize the promise of\ngravitational waves for constraining the supranuclear EOS.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 22 Oct 2019 02:50:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-03-11"}
