 break phase occurs directly after the plateau. We\nsuggest that this sequence of events can be explained by a rapid deceleration\nof the jet with $t_d\\lesssim 40$ s due to the high density of the environment\n($\\approx 100$ cm$^{-3}$) followed by reactivation of the central engine which\ncauses the flare and powers the plateau phase.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 22 Oct 2019 03:00:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-01-08"}
