 and socioeconomic\nstatus had no moderating role, and there was no evidence for park satisfaction\nas a mediator between park features and park use. Results suggest diverse park\nfeatures are associated with park satisfaction and park use, but this did not\nvary by ethnicity or socioeconomic status. The reduction of incivilities should\nbe prioritised where the aim is to encourage park satisfaction and park use.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 22 Oct 2019 12:32:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-10-23"}
