d by\nthis effect typically remain below the 1 ppm level. If a mass calibration using\ntwo or more ion species is possible during the measurement, the effect becomes\nnegligible for appropriate choices of reference masses.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 22 Oct 2019 12:16:33 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 27 Apr 2020 12:30:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-04-28"}
